MODULE 0 – MOQUI TASK IMPLEMENTATION
===================================

This repository contains the implementation of Module 0 tasks using the Moqui Framework.
The work is divided into three custom Moqui components as described below.


COMPONENT STRUCTURE
-------------------

runtime/component/
│
├── moqui-training/
│   ├── component.xml
│   ├── data/
│   ├── entity/
│   ├── screen/
│   ├── service/
│
│
├── party/
│   ├── component.xml
│   ├── data/
│   ├── entity/
│   ├── screen/
│   ├── service/
|   ├── MoquiConf.xml/
│  
│
└── tutorial/
    ├── MoquiConf.xml
    ├── data/
    ├── entity/
    ├── screen/
    ├── script/
    ├── service/
  


TASK-WISE IMPLEMENTATION
=======================


TASK 0 – ENVIRONMENT & COMPONENT SETUP
--------------------------------------
• Moqui Framework setup completed
• Custom components created under runtime/component
• Components registered using component.xml
• Verified components load successfully at runtime


TASK 1 – moqui-training COMPONENT
---------------------------------
Component Name: moqui-training

• Created as part of Task 1 of Module 0
• Purpose:
  - Understand Moqui component structure
  - Verify component loading
  - Basic screen creation
• connected to default h2 database


TASK 2 – MYSQL DATABASE CONNECTION
----------------------------------
Component: party

• Connected Moqui to MySQL database named `moqui`
• Changes made in MoquiDevConf.xml (NOT committed to Git)
• Datasource configuration added inside entity-facade:

<datasource group-name="transactional" database-conf-name="mysql8" schema-name="moqui">
    <inline-jdbc
        jdbc-driver="com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver"
        jdbc-uri="jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/moqui?autoReconnect=true&amp;useUnicode=true&amp;characterEncoding=UTF-8&amp;useSSL=false&amp;allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&amp;serverTimezone=UTC"
        jdbc-username="moqui"
        jdbc-password="changeme">
    </inline-jdbc>
</datasource>

• Database connection verified successfully


TASK 3 – ENTITY CREATION & SEED DATA
------------------------------------
Component: party

• Created custom entities (Party, Person, etc.)
• Defined entity relationships
• Added seed/demo data using data XML
• Verified data insertion in MySQL database


TASK 4 – DISPLAY PARTY DATA ON SCREEN
-------------------------------------
Component: party

• Created a screen to display Party entity records
• Used list-form to show data in tabular format
• Data fetched using entity-find
• Party records successfully visible on UI


TASK 5 – CREATE PARTY USING DEFAULT SERVICE
-------------------------------------------
Component: party

• Created a form screen
• Used Moqui default create service
• Form submits data directly to database
• Party records created successfully via UI


TASK 6 – CUSTOM SERVICE FOR PERSON ENTITY
-----------------------------------------
Component: party

• Created a custom service to insert Person entity data
• Service tested using:
  - Moqui screen form
  - REST API endpoint
  - Postman
  - Swagger Api
• Data successfully stored in database


TUTORIAL COMPONENT
==================
Component Name: tutorial

• Created for practice and learning purposes
• Based on Moqui Quick Tutorial
• Used to understand:
  - Entities
  - Services
  - Screens
  - REST APIs
• Not part of evaluation tasks


SUMMARY
=======
• Module 0 tasks completed from Task 0 to Task 6
• Proper component separation followed
• Database configuration handled securely
• Screens, entities, and services implemented as per instructions
